'''237''' ('''two hundred [and] thirty-seven''') is the [[natural number]] following [[236 (number)|236]] and preceding [[238 (number)|238]].
{{Infobox number
| number = 237
| prime = no
}}

237 is a [[lucky number]],<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A000959}}</ref> and one of the numbers in [[Aronson's sequence]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A005224}}</ref>

The 237th [[square pyramidal number]], 4465475, is also a sum of two smaller square pyramidal numbers. There are only four smaller numbers (55, 70, 147, and 226) with the same property.<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A053719}}</ref>

==In culture==

===In film and television===

237 is the number of a haunted room in the Overlook Hotel in the Stanley Kubrick's film [[The Shining (film)|The Shining]], and part of a network of interrelated numbers within the film<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wabgZNgT9OgC&q=42#v=snippet&q=42&f=false|title=Kubrick: Inside a Film Artist's Maze|last=Nelson|first=Thomas Allen|date=2000-01-01|p=325-326|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=0253213908|language=en}}</ref> (see [[The Shining (film)#Room number]] and the documentary [[Room 237]]).{{importance-inline}}

