In [[mathematics]], in the [[representation theory]] of [[algebraic group|algebraic]] [[Group (mathematics)|groups]], a '''Grosshans subgroup''', named after [[Frank Grosshans]], is an algebraic [[subgroup]] of an algebraic group that is an [[observable subgroup]] for which the [[ring (mathematics)|ring]] of functions on the quotient [[algebraic variety|variety]] is [[Finitely generated algebra|finitely generated]].<ref>{{citation|title=Lectures on Invariant Theory|volume=296|series=London Mathematical Society Lecture Note Series|first=Igor|last=Dolgachev|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2003|isbn=9780521525480|page=50|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=B9S_0iPvfrUC&pg=PA50}}.</ref>
