'''William McFadden Orr''', [[Fellow of the Royal Society|FRS]]<ref name="frs">{{Cite journal | last1 = Conway | first1 = A. W. | title = William McFadden Orr. 1866-1934 | doi = 10.1098/rsbm.1935.0019 | journal = [[Obituary Notices of Fellows of the Royal Society]] | volume = 1 | issue = 4 | pages = 559 | year = 1935 | pmid = | jstor = 768986| pmc = }}</ref> (2 May 1866 &ndash; 14 August 1934) was a [[United Kingdom|British]] and Irish [[mathematician]].
He was born in [[Comber]], [[County Down]] and educated at [[Methodist College Belfast]] and [[Queen's College, Belfast]] under [[John Purser (mathematician)|John Purser]], before entering [[St John's College, Cambridge]] and graduating as [[Senior Wrangler]] in 1888.<ref>{{acad|id=OR885WM|name=Orr, William McFadden}}</ref> He was elected a fellow of his college, and became a [[Fellow of the Royal Society]] in 1909.
He was appointed professor of mathematics at the [[Royal College of Science for Ireland]] in 1892 and professor of [[pure mathematics]] and [[applied mathematics]] when the college merged with [[University College Dublin]] in 1926. He retired in 1933 and died in 1934, and is interred in [[Mount Jerome Cemetery]], Dublin.
